  "detailed_description": "You come home from a long day at work, go to bed, and when you wake up, something's very different...<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/72c702b1a1bb9e7d30917f94cd3a30af.webp?t=1745162689\" width=218 height=29 /></span><br>Liminality is a <span class=\"bb_strike\">relaxing</span> liminal <strong>horror</strong> game focused on exploration, the poolrooms and other liminal spaces.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/0b1b6f49920b1081358bb0e22f500cba.poster.avif?t=1745162689\" width=540 height=406 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/0b1b6f49920b1081358bb0e22f500cba.webm?t=1745162689\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/0b1b6f49920b1081358bb0e22f500cba.mp4?t=1745162689\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><i>*the game might look different based on your graphics level and graphics card</i><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/2c42055de9af3f0a6d35f4c167beb6f9.webp?t=1745162689\" width=293 height=26 /></span><br>The game revolves entirely around Liminal Spaces, but what exactly are they? Liminality refers to something stuck between two different places or states. Liminal Spaces embody this, serving as areas in a state of transition. But when you stumble upon these places devoid of life, it's eerie. You'd expect company, but it's just you... or at least you believe so.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/ec30985905b7d7e5422051704f9656ba.webp?t=1745162689\" width=233 height=27 /></span><br>The poolrooms are a series of big, dimly lit spaces filled with lukewarm water. These eerie, empty areas seem to stretch on forever, mixing a weird sense of calm with creeping dread. As you wander through the quiet water and deserted halls, the unsettling silence makes you wonder if you're really alone.",
  "about_the_game": "You come home from a long day at work, go to bed, and when you wake up, something's very different...<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/72c702b1a1bb9e7d30917f94cd3a30af.webp?t=1745162689\" width=218 height=29 /></span><br>Liminality is a <span class=\"bb_strike\">relaxing</span> liminal <strong>horror</strong> game focused on exploration, the poolrooms and other liminal spaces.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/0b1b6f49920b1081358bb0e22f500cba.poster.avif?t=1745162689\" width=540 height=406 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/0b1b6f49920b1081358bb0e22f500cba.webm?t=1745162689\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/0b1b6f49920b1081358bb0e22f500cba.mp4?t=1745162689\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><i>*the game might look different based on your graphics level and graphics card</i><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/2c42055de9af3f0a6d35f4c167beb6f9.webp?t=1745162689\" width=293 height=26 /></span><br>The game revolves entirely around Liminal Spaces, but what exactly are they? Liminality refers to something stuck between two different places or states. Liminal Spaces embody this, serving as areas in a state of transition. But when you stumble upon these places devoid of life, it's eerie. You'd expect company, but it's just you... or at least you believe so.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2916260/extras/ec30985905b7d7e5422051704f9656ba.webp?t=1745162689\" width=233 height=27 /></span><br>The poolrooms are a series of big, dimly lit spaces filled with lukewarm water. These eerie, empty areas seem to stretch on forever, mixing a weird sense of calm with creeping dread. As you wander through the quiet water and deserted halls, the unsettling silence makes you wonder if you're really alone.",
